As you didn&#39;t provide any code in your question, consider, for example, you have a map as shown below:

```java
Map&lt;String, Object&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
map.put(&quot;firstName&quot;, &quot;John&quot;);
map.put(&quot;lastName&quot;, &quot;Doe&quot;);
map.put(&quot;emails&quot;, Arrays.asList(&quot;johndoe@mail.com&quot;, &quot;john.doe@mail.com&quot;));
map.put(&quot;birthday&quot;, LocalDate.of(1990, 1, 1));
```

And you want to map it to and instance of `Contact`:

```java
@Data
public class Contact {
    private String firstName;
    private String lastName;
    private List&lt;String&gt; emails;
}
```

It could be achieved with the following code:

```java
ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
mapper.disable(DeserializationFeature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES);
Contact contact = mapper.convertValue(map, Contact.class);
```

In the example above, the map has a `birthday` key, which cannot be mapped to any field of the `Contact` class. To prevent the serialization from failing, the [`FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES`][1] feature has been disabled.

---

Alternatively, you could annotate the `Contact` class with [`@JsonIgnoreProperties`][2] and set [`ignoreUnknown`][3] to `true`:

```java
@Data
@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)
public class Contact {
    ...
}
```

And then perform the conversion:

```java
ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
Contact contact = mapper.convertValue(map, Contact.class);
```

---

To convert the `Contact` instance back to a map, you can use:

```java
ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
Map&lt;String, Object&gt; map = mapper.convertValue(contact, 
        new TypeReference&lt;Map&lt;String, Object&gt;&gt;() {});
```


  [1]: https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-databind/javadoc/2.9/com/fasterxml/jackson/databind/DeserializationFeature.html#FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES
  [2]: https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-annotations/javadoc/2.9/com/fasterxml/jackson/annotation/JsonIgnoreProperties.html
  [3]: https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-annotations/javadoc/2.9/com/fasterxml/jackson/annotation/JsonIgnoreProperties.html#ignoreUnknown()

